<poem>
  <phead>
    <ptitle>Sonnet 21</ptitle>
    <author>
      <first-name>William</first-name>
      <last-name>Shakespeare</last-name>
    </author>
  </phead>
  <pbody>
    <stanza>
      <line>So is it not with me as with that muse</line>
      <line>Stirred by a painted beauty to his<phoneme category="b">verse</phoneme></line>
      <line>Who heaven it self for ornament doth use</line>
      <line>And every fair with his fair doth<phoneme category="b">rehearse</phoneme></line>
      <line>Making a couplement<phoneme category="c">compare</phoneme><phoneme category="c">compare</phoneme><phoneme category="c">compare</phoneme></line>
      <line>With sun and moon with earth and sea rich<phoneme category="d">gems</phoneme></line>
      <line>With April first born<phoneme category="c">rare</phoneme><phoneme category="c">rare</phoneme><phoneme category="c">rare</phoneme><phoneme category="c">rare</phoneme><phoneme category="c">rare</phoneme></line>
      <line>That heaven air in this huge rondure<phoneme category="d">hems</phoneme></line>
      <line>O let me true in love but truly<phoneme category="e">write</phoneme></line>
      <line>And then believe<phoneme category="f">fair</phoneme><phoneme category="f">fair</phoneme><phoneme category="f">fair</phoneme><phoneme category="f">fair</phoneme><phoneme category="f">fair</phoneme><phoneme category="f">fair</phoneme></line>
      <line>As any mother child though not so<phoneme category="e">bright</phoneme></line>
      <line>As those<phoneme category="f">air</phoneme><phoneme category="f">air</phoneme><phoneme category="f">air</phoneme><phoneme category="f">air</phoneme><phoneme category="f">air</phoneme><phoneme category="f">air</phoneme></line>
      <line>Let them say more that like of hearsay<phoneme category="g">well</phoneme></line>
      <line>I will not praise that purpose not to<phoneme category="g">sell</phoneme></line>
    </stanza>
  </pbody>
</poem>